description:
Introduction to Verilog HDL: Verilog as HDL, Levels of Design Description, Concurrency, Hierarchical Modelling: Top-down and Bottom-up design methodology, differences between modules and module instances, parts of a simulation, design block, stimulus block; Functional Test; Basic Concepts: Lexical conventions, data types, system tasks; Modules and Ports: Module definition, port declaration, port connection, hierarchical name referencing;
Modelling Techniques: Gate-level Modelling: Modelling using basic Verilog gate Primitives, Description of and/or and buf/not type gates, rise, fall and turn-off delays, min, max, and typical delays. Dataflow Modelling: Continuous assignments, Delay specification, expressions, operators. Behavioural Modelling: Procedural Assignments, Initial and always blocks, blocking and non-blocking statements, delay control, conditional statements, Multiway branching, loops, sequential and parallel blocks;

Advanced Topics: Timing and Delays: Specify blocks, timing checks; Generate blocks, Synthesis: Operators and constructs, typical issues during synthesis, synthesis design flow

Verilog HDL based implementation of digital RTL sub-systems: Design, simulation and functional testing of following digital logic (combinational and sequential) sub-systems using Verilog HDL: Decoder, MUX, Comparators, Combinational shifters, Adders, Multipliers, Counters, Shift-Registers, Moore Finite State Machine, Memories, Communication protocols
